reviews.review_text:
This Show Smokes!! The boys were firing on all cylinders that night!  Jerry’s voice sounds as good as ever during 1982.  Believe me…they miss his voice as much of his awesome guitar-playing prowess!  Just listen to his voice/guitar on They Love Each Other and Peggy-O.  Simply amazing!!  Bobby and Brent are in high-gear, and this Spring tour was just revving up!!

Check out the file, gd1982-04-19.89314.txt, to see the improvements made to this show.  This Matrix is the best-sounding source for this concert!  60% SBD and 40% AUD.  What a great mix!  Great job, Kevin Tobin!  You are the fucking shit!!

This show at the Baltimore Civic Center in Baltimore, MD is easily one of the best shows from 1982.  One of the future "Road Trips" releases should be this show, plus the previous two nights at the Hartford Civic Center in Hartford, CT.  I would put these 3 shows up against almost any 3 consecutive nights (except of course 5/7, 5/8, and 5/9 from 1977 – LOL)!!

The 2nd set of this show ranks right up there with any Grateful Dead 2nd set of any show I’ve ever heard!  I mean, just look at this fucking set, everybody!

Set 2
d2t01 - Feel Like A Stranger
d2t01 - Franklin's Tower
d2t01 - Estimated Prophet
d2t01 - Terrapin Station
d2t01 - Drums
d3t01 - Raven Space
d3t02 - The Wheel
d3t03 - Truckin'
d3t04 - Stella Blue
d3t05 - Around And Around
d3t06 - Good Lovin'

Encore
d3t07 - Brokedown Palace

Feel Like A Stranger --> Franklin’s Tower --> Estimated Prophet --> Terrapin Station, is absolutely ridiculous!!

The Raven Space is mind-altering.  You definitely should download this show.  The Wheel --> Truckin' --> Stella Blue --> Around And Around --> Good Lovin' --> Brokedown Palace are some of the best versions I've ever heard.  I sure haven't heard many Stella Blue's that can hold a candle to this one, people!!  And the Good Lovin’ kicks some serious ass!!

Check out my other reviews from awesome Grateful Dead shows!!

Danny from Northern Virginia outside of Washington, D.C.
East-Coast Deadhead

PEACE-OUT!

I agree RFKROX Went to Durham, Norfolk and this one on that tour. They were on fire from start to finish. Weirdest space I ever saw. Love it. I highly recommend this show for all. Baltimore wasn't big on their tour schedule, this was the last of only 6 shows there but when they did play there, they tore it up.

Phil: More nitrous!

This imo is an epic show in Dead history. Every fan should have this in their collection to get a feel of what they were really all about.

Jerry rocks and eases the soul when in pain!

At least my soul.
